9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 237, L.D. 558, “An Act to Strengthen
10 Consumer Protections by Prohibiting the Report of Medical Debt on Consumer Reports”
11 Amend the bill by inserting after the enacting clause the following:
12 'Sec. 1. 10 MRSA §1308, sub-§3-A is enacted to read:
13 3-A. Debt buyer. "Debt buyer" has the same meaning as in Title 32, section 11002,
14 subsection 5-A.
15 Sec. 2. 10 MRSA §1308, sub-§3-B is enacted to read:
16 3-B. Debt collector. "Debt collector" has the same meaning as in Title 32, section
17 11002, subsection 6.
18 Sec. 3. 10 MRSA §1308, sub-§4-A is enacted to read:
19 4-A. Medical creditor. "Medical creditor" means an entity that provides health care
20 services and to whom a consumer incurs medical debt or an entity that provided health care
21 services to a consumer and to whom the consumer previously owed medical debt if the
22 medical debt has been purchased by one or more debt buyers.
23 Sec. 4. 10 MRSA §1308, sub-§4-B is enacted to read:
24 4-B. Medical debt. "Medical debt" has the same meaning as in Title 32, section
25 11002, subsection 7-A.'
26 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 4 in the first line (page 1, line 4 in L.D.) by
27 striking out the following: "expenses" and inserting the following: 'expenses debt'
28 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 4 in the 3rd line (page 1, line 6 in L.D.) by
29 striking out the following: "expenses" and inserting the following: 'expenses debt'
30 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 4 in paragraph A in the first line (page 1, line
31 7 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "debt from medical expenses" and inserting the
32 following: 'debt from medical expenses medical debt'
