COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 237, L.D. 558
1 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 4 in paragraph A in the last line (page 1, line
2 9 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "reported" the following: 'and a medical creditor,
3 debt collector or debt buyer may not report a consumer's medical debt to a consumer
4 reporting agency'
5 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
6 number to read consecutively.
7 SUMMARY
88 This amendment prohibits the reporting of medical debt on a consumer report and
99 clarifies that medical debt has the same definition as currently used in the Maine Fair Debt
1100 Collection Practices Act. The amendment also prohibits a debt collector, debt buyer or an
1111 entity that provides health care services from reporting medical debt to a consumer
1122 reporting agency.
